                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d659">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">812.52/2804: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Mexico</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Boal</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Mexico</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1938-06-06T17:00:00-06:00"
                            >June 6, 1938—5 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/>[Received June 7—1:10 a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>248. Yepis’ telegram June 3, 5 p.m., and my 246, June 4, 1 p.m. General Hay told
                    me yesterday that he had urgently requested no definitive dotations be made of
                    American property in Yaqui Valley at this time. He said he had communicated at
                    noon on June 4 with the Agrarian Department where he was told that nothing was
                    known of any plan to make these dotations definitive and that he also
                    communicated by telephone with Licenciado Beteta at San Luis Potosí asking him
                    to take up the matter with the President and with Licenciado Gabino Vazquez,
                    head of the Agrarian Department.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Boal</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
